                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 834.00/109.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-10-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 5, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Congress confirmed Liberato Rojas as Provisional President for the entire new
                    electoral term. The formality of an election was dispensed with. Dr. Carlos
                    Isasi is Minister for Foreign Affairs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grevstad.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
